{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.31",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 31 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:1",
      "text": "The words of Lemuel, king of Massa, which his mother taught him:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:2",
      "text": "What, my son? What, son of my womb? What, son of my vows?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:3",
      "text": "Give not your strength to women, your ways to those who destroy kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:4",
      "text": "It is not for kings, O Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine, or for rulers to desire strong drink;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:5",
      "text": "lest they drink and forget what has been decreed, and pervert the rights of all the afflicted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:6",
      "text": "Give strong drink to him who is perishing, and wine to those in bitter distress;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:7",
      "text": "let them drink and forget their poverty, and remember their misery no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:8",
      "text": "Open your mouth for the dumb, for the rights of all who are left desolate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:9",
      "text": "Open your mouth, judge righteously, maintain the rights of the poor and needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:10",
      "text": "A good wife who can find? She is far more precious than jewels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:11",
      "text": "The heart of her husband trusts in her, and he will have no lack of gain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:12",
      "text": "She does him good, and not harm, all the days of her life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:13",
      "text": "She seeks wool and flax, and works with willing hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:14",
      "text": "She is like the ships of the merchant, she brings her food from afar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:15",
      "text": "She rises while it is yet night and provides food for her household and tasks for her maidens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:16",
      "text": "She considers a field and buys it; with the fruit of her hands she plants a vineyard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:17",
      "text": "She girds her loins with strength and makes her arms strong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:18",
      "text": "She perceives that her merchandise is profitable. Her lamp does not go out at night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:19",
      "text": "She puts her hands to the distaff, and her hands hold the spindle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:20",
      "text": "She opens her hand to the poor, and reaches out her hands to the needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:21",
      "text": "She is not afraid of snow for her household, for all her household are clothed in scarlet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:22",
      "text": "She makes herself coverings; her clothing is fine linen and purple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:23",
      "text": "Her husband is known in the gates, when he sits among the elders of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:24",
      "text": "She makes linen garments and sells them; she delivers girdles to the merchant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:25",
      "text": "Strength and dignity are her clothing, and she laughs at the time to come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:26",
      "text": "She opens her mouth with wisdom, and the teaching of kindness is on her tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:27",
      "text": "She looks well to the ways of her household, and does not eat the bread of idleness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:28",
      "text": "Her children rise up and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praises her:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:29",
      "text": "“Many women have done excellently, but you surpass them all.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:30",
      "text": "Charm is deceitful, and beauty is vain, but a woman who fears the Lord is to be praised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.31.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:31",
      "text": "Give her of the fruit of her hands, and let her works praise her in the gates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
